I was driving on a lonesome road and saw a small famished dog in the woods. I thought about how it probably had to cannibalize its siblings, will hunt field mice, fight other dogs to mate with a female and restart the cycle, before dying from hunger and cold in next winter's time

Its other option would be to be taken to a no-kill shelter, castrated, fed well with bulk dog-food, sit in its warm cage, never fight, never procreate, die well-cared for in old age. I am sure the dog would pick the wilderness, suffering, cannibalism, blood rather than a shelter.
This is far better than my own tweet, I have to admit

What is the ideal then? Warmth, numerous offspring, well-fedness of all, fighting without shedding blood as sport, exploration of wilderness without suffering its cold and always having a home, health, a hundred contradictions of Heaven. Street dogs dream of New Jerusalem too.
